caption: I usually am quite pleased with this establishment. But they very seriously overlooked something with my sandwiches when I purchased them for my ENTIRE CREW  at work and praised their goodness. A small staff of six, I bought 2 spinach aracinis, meatball sandwich, Italiano, and 2 Diavolos with extra Genoa salami and hot giardinera. Some of the meat on the latter sandwiches still had plastic wrap on it and we ended up having it throughout our sandwiches....Bad...and I can't go back until Monday, because they are closed on Sundays......feel bad, but people have to be careful....and this was bad and embarrassing 😢after having told my colleagues how much I praise these sandwiches....

They have cheeses , gelato, espresso and petite sweets and a whole fridge filled with pre packaged pasta! Such an awesome shop, ENJOY!

I've been on a search for quality Italian pasta and goods after returning from a two week trip to Italy.  While L'Appetito does a good job carrying a variety of imported Italian goods, they only had one pasta on the menu and that rotates on a daily basis.  While I'm a fan of daily, fresh pasta, it had better be darn good if you're only offering one a day.  Today they had penne with tomato sauce and some mozzarella and parmesan cheese on top.  The pasta was cooked well, but the sauce wasn't anything special and overall the dish was something I'd expect from a chain Italian restaurant (see: Sbarro's).  I hear good things about their paninis and I'll go back to try one of them out and another pasta, but for now this is at best a 3 star option mainly because of the imported Italian items offered and not because of actual food quality.

This is for L'Appetito at Midway near gate b1: Walked around midway in our terminal to try and find some good food. This place seemed pretty straight forward and I love paninis! Too bad they were served COLD. Took the food on the way back to our gate to sit down and eat since the food lobby was too full. So, to be fair, I did not give them a chance to rectify the situation. It looked like they grilled the bread then assembled the Panini rather than putting it together and then grilling it. Also got a little salad out of their case- soggy croutons. Is there anything more cruel? Save your money for another place. I just wasted $35 there.
